<subSubSection id="C30E6565C917FFA07EC2FE7E1A3A1229" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAB36EEC917FFA07EC2FE7E1DF4127C" blockId="104.[151,1436,152,526]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis id="B960EAFCC917FFA07EC2FE7E1F7611B2" bold="true" box="[198,319,422,448]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Remarks.</emphasis>
The monotypic genus was originally described from fossil records and Recent material from the bathyal zone of the 
<collectingRegion id="49D0F80CC917FFA07FA3FE151FB31195" box="[423,506,461,487]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">Azores</collectingRegion>
and the Indian Ocean (
<bibRefCitation id="EF854B1FC917FFA07D0DFE151D971195" author="Zibrowius, H." box="[777,990,461,487]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105" pagination="183 - 190" refId="ref69925" refString="Zibrowius, H. (1979 b) Vitreotubus digeronimoi n. g., n. sp. (Polychaeta Serpulidae) du Pleistocene inferieur de la Sicile et de l'etage bathyal des Acores et de l'Ocean Indien. Tethys, 9, 183 - 190." type="journal article" year="1979">Zibrowius, 1979b</bibRefCitation>
), more recent records are given by ten Hove (1994). It has a very characteristically shaped transparent tube.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAB36EEC917FFA07E93FD991A3A1229" blockId="104.[151,1139,577,603]" box="[151,1139,577,603]" pageId="104" pageNumber="105">
